; Recursive stratum (tc over `edge`) feeding a DOWNSTREAM differential
; consumer (`marked`) that joins tc's output against another
; @differential base relation, itself feeding a further derived relation.
; This exercises the BUILDFRONTIERS producer -> consumer seam
; (plan.md :746-757 "a recursive->downstream-differential program"):
; tc is stratum-recursive; its outDel/outAdd frontiers, once (c) actually
; populates them with real net deletions (not permanently-empty, per
; pseudo-c-spec.md FLAG-K/ #5), must be correctly consumed by a HIGHER,
; itself-differential stratum's own seed phase. A wrong BUILDFRONTIERS
; wiring (frontiers not populated, or populated but not consumed, or
; consumed with the wrong sign) changes `flagged`'s final membership
; without necessarily tripping any single-stratum counter assert, since
; the corruption is a cross-stratum WIRING bug, not a within-stratum
; counting bug -- exactly the class of defect the sensitivity argument
; below calls out as requiring an END-STATE check (this fixture) rather
; than relying on tc's own commit asserts (which see a perfectly
; consistent tc regardless of whether its frontier is being read
; correctly downstream).
#message add_edge(u64 From, u64 To) @differential.
#message watch(u64 X) @differential.

#local tc(From, To).
#local edge(From, To).
#local marked(X).
#local flagged(X).

edge(From, To) : add_edge(From, To).

tc(From, To) : edge(From, To).
tc(From, To) : tc(From, X), tc(X, To).

; Downstream differential consumer: X is marked if it is tc-reachable
; from some watched node AND watch(X) holds too (a differential join
; against tc's output, forcing a real dependency on tc's outDel/outAdd
; frontiers rather than only its final row set).
marked(X) : tc(W, X), watch(W).
flagged(X) : marked(X), watch(X).

#query flagged_out(free u64 X).
flagged_out(X) : flagged(X).
